<div class="pf1e-util-help-content">
  <h1>Actor Script Calls</h1>

  <p>
    Actor Script Calls are JavaScript snippets that run automatically when specific events occur
    on an actor. They work similarly to Item Script Calls but are configured directly on the actor
    and react to combat, movement, and update events.
  </p>

  <h2>Variables</h2>
  <p>The following variables are always available inside every script call.</p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Name</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>actor</code></td><td>The actor this script call belongs to.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>combat</code></td><td>The active Combat instance. Available on all combat events.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>token</code></td><td>The token document. Available on <em>Move</em> events.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>position</code></td><td>The final <code>{x, y}</code> position. Available on <em>Move</em> events.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>updateData</code></td><td>The update delta. Available on <em>Update</em> events.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Events</h2>

  <h3>Turn Start</h3>
  <p>Called when it becomes this actor's turn in combat.</p>

  <h3>Turn End</h3>
  <p>Called when this actor's turn ends in combat.</p>

  <h3>Round Start</h3>
  <p>Called at the start of each combat round for every actor participating in that combat.</p>

  <h3>Round End</h3>
  <p>Called at the end of each combat round for every actor participating in that combat.</p>

  <h3>Combat Start</h3>
  <p>Called when combat begins for every actor participating in that combat.</p>

  <h3>Combat End</h3>
  <p>Called when combat ends for every actor that was participating.</p>

  <h3>Update</h3>
  <p>
    Called whenever the actor's data is updated. The script receives <code>updateData</code>
    containing only the changed fields. Updates triggered by the script itself are ignored
    to prevent infinite loops.
  </p>

  <h3>Move</h3>
  <p>
    Called when one of the actor's tokens is moved. Fires at the final position only — not
    during animation. Receives <code>token</code> and <code>position</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>Example</h2>
  <pre><code>// Turn Start — log a reminder
console.log(`It is ${actor.name}'s turn!`);

// Move — react to final position
console.log(`${actor.name} moved to`, position);

// Update — react to HP changes
if (updateData?.system?.attributes?.hp) {
  console.log(`${actor.name} HP changed`);
}</code></pre>
</div>
